quiet /ˈkwaɪət/

(quieting,quieted,quieter,quiets,quietest) 

1. ADJ Someone or something that is quiet makes only a small amount of noise. 轻声的; 安静的 

例： Tania kept the children reasonably quiet and contented. 塔妮娅把孩子们料理得安心而满足。 

2. quietly ADV 轻声地; 安静地 [ADV with v] 

例： 'This is goodbye, isn't it?' she said quietly. “这就算告别了，不是吗？”她轻声地说道。 

3. ADJ If a place is quiet , there is very little noise there. 寂静的 

例： She was received in a small, quiet office. 她在一间寂静的小办公室里受到接见。 

4. quietness N-UNCOUNT 寂静 

例： I miss the quietness of the countryside. 我怀念农村的寂静。 

5. ADJ If a place, situation, or time is quiet , there is no excitement, activity, or trouble. 平静的; 清静的 

例： ...a quiet rural backwater. …一个清静的乡间隐蔽处。 

6. quietly ADV 平静地; 清静地 [ADV with v] 

例： His most prized time, though, will be spent quietly on his farm. 不过，他最珍贵的时光将在自己的农场上平静地度过。 

7. N-UNCOUNT Quiet is silence. 安静 

例： He called for quiet and announced that the next song was in our honour. 他要求静下来，并宣布下一首歌是献给我们的。 

8. ADJ If you are quiet , you are not saying anything. 不出声的 [v-link ADJ] 

例： I told them to be quiet and go to sleep. 我叫他们不要说话，去睡觉。 

9. quietly ADV 不出声地 [ADV with v] 

例： Amy stood quietly in the doorway watching him. 艾米一声不响地站在门口看着他。 

10. ADJ A quiet person behaves in a calm way and is not easily made angry or upset. 冷静的; 不易动怒的 

例： He's a nice quiet man. 他是个冷静的好男人。 

11. V-T/V-I [美国英语] →see quieten , quieten 

12. PHRASE If you keep quiet about something or keep something quiet , you do not say anything about it. 保守秘密 

例： I told her to keep quiet about it. 我叫她对此保守秘密。 

13. PHRASE If something is done on the quiet , it is done secretly or in such a way that people do not notice it. 秘密地 

例： She'd promised to give him driving lessons, on the quiet, when no one could see. 她答应在无人看见时秘密地给他上驾驶课。

